just_use player.py

# label: VESTIGIAL (superseded by lynrummy_elm_player/client.py)
# role: legacy — console LynRummy player, pre-Elm era

The original Python LynRummy player, built to talk to the
pre-Elm Angry Gopher game host. Polls game events, tracks
board + hand locally, can send moves as any authenticated
player. Used for spectating, advising, and console play.

## Status (FIRM)

VESTIGIAL. Replaced by `tools/lynrummy_elm_player/client.py`
and `auto_player.py`, which talk to the Elm-era wire
(`/gopher/lynrummy-elm/`). This file targets the pre-Elm
game host. Likely does NOT work against the current server.

Candidate for removal. Keeping the file rather than deleting
preserves the console-UI pattern for anyone wanting a
reference, but a fresh reader should NOT use it as a starting
point.

## Surface (historical)

```
python3 tools/lynrummy_player/player.py --game-id N \
    --email EMAIL --api-key KEY [--host URL]
```

## Pointers

- Successor: `tools/lynrummy_elm_player/client.py` +
  `auto_player.py`.
- Memory: `project_lynrummy_elm_port_status.md` — Elm port
  is functionally complete; this pre-Elm client is the
  opposite end of that transition.
